This paper discusses Estimation of Distribution Algorithms (EDAs), which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization. The paper also connects EDAs to Expectation Maximization (EM), which is a well-established statistical method. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses optimization and convergence properties, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
